reviews.review_text: Complete Brokedown Palace Great show overall, sound quality's ok but obviously not as good as the sbd that's out there.  This aud recording has the full version of Brokedown Palace that gets cut off halfway through in the sbd, though.  Ken Kesey's son, a wrestler at U of Oregon, was killed when the team van drove off a cliff not long before this show in 1984.  Kesey was in attendance at this show.  At the end, the entire band turned toward him and played Brokedown.  In a later interview, Kesey recounted with tears in his eyes that it wasn't until that moment that he really understood what art was. He said that "All my life I thought art was this [he stuck a fist in the air]. But at that moment I realized that art was really this [he made a hugging motion]."  It's great to have this moment in history available in its full version on this recording.
